# keyboard_hook

A modular, threaded, and process-isolated Windows keyboard hook library built on `ctypes`.

## Structure

```
keyboard_hook/
├── __init__.py      # Public API
├── constants.py     # WM_* messages, VK key name map
├── winfunc.py       # Declarative Win32 function base class
├── bindings.py      # All Win32 API bindings
├── events.py        # KeyEvent dataclass + KBDLLHOOKSTRUCT
├── hook.py          # Base KeyboardHook (blocking)
├── threaded.py      # ThreadedKeyboardHook + HotkeyHook
├── process.py       # ProcessKeyboardHook
└── example.py       # Usage examples
```

## Quick Start

### HotkeyHook (threaded, recommended for most use cases)

```python
from keyboard_hook import HotkeyHook

hook = HotkeyHook()
hook.register("ESCAPE", hook.stop)
hook.register("A", lambda: print("A pressed"))
hook.register("F5", lambda: print("F5!"), on_keyup=True)  # fire on release
hook.listen(lambda e: print(e))  # raw listener for every event

with hook:
    hook.wait()
```

### ProcessKeyboardHook (isolated process, always stoppable)

```python
from keyboard_hook import ProcessKeyboardHook

hook = ProcessKeyboardHook()
hook.register("ESCAPE", hook.stop)
hook.register("A", lambda: print("A pressed"))

with hook:
    hook.wait()

# Force kill if needed (e.g. from another thread)
hook.kill()
```

### KeyboardHook (raw, blocking)

```python
from keyboard_hook import KeyboardHook, KeyEvent

def on_key(event: KeyEvent) -> bool:
    print(event)
    return False  # don't suppress

with KeyboardHook(on_key=on_key) as hook:
    hook.run()   # blocks until hook.stop() is called
```

## Key Names

Keys can be registered by name or raw `vk_code` int:

```python
hook.register("ESCAPE", ...)
hook.register("SPACE", ...)
hook.register("F5", ...)
hook.register("A", ...)       # A-Z supported
hook.register("1", ...)       # 0-9 supported
hook.register(0x1B, ...)      # raw vk_code also works
```

Full list available in `keyboard_hook.VK`.

## KeyEvent Properties

```python
event.vk_code    # virtual key code
event.scan_code  # hardware scan code
event.flags      # raw flags
event.time       # timestamp
event.is_keydown # True on key press
event.is_keyup   # True on key release
event.is_injected  # True if sent by software
event.is_extended  # True for numpad/arrow keys
```

## Class Overview

| Class | Thread | Process | Use when |
|---|---|---|---|
| `KeyboardHook` | Caller | Same | Full control, manual threading |
| `ThreadedKeyboardHook` | Background | Same | Simple background hook |
| `HotkeyHook` | Background | Same | Hotkey registration + wait() |
| `ProcessKeyboardHook` | Background | Child | Must always be killable |
